        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "The minor scale form having major sixth and major seventh above tonic to be called Melodic Minor.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000060_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000060_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "Illustrative examples.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "low",
        "speed": "very fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000065_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000065_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "The Committee finds that the words: Pulse and Beat are in general use as synonymous terms, meaning one of the succession of throbs or impulses of which we are conscious when listening to music.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000065_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000065_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "Each of these pulses or beats has an exact point of beginning, a duration, and an exact point of ending, the latter coincident with the beginning of the next pulse or beat.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000067_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000067_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "One of these words, Beat, is also in universal use, meaning one of a series of physical motions by means of which a conductor holds his group of performers to a uniform movement.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000068_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000068_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "When thus used it becomes a term of eye.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000069_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000069_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "The conductor's baton, if it is to be authoritative, cannot wander about through the whole duration of the pulse but must move quickly to a point of comparative repose, remaining until just before the arrival of the next pulse when it again makes a rapid swing, finishing coincidently with the initial tone (or silence) of the new pulse.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000070_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000070_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "Thus it is practically the end of the conductor's beat that marks the beginning of the pulse.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000071_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000071_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "The Committee is of opinion that Beat might preferably be used as indicating the outward sign.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000073_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000073_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "This term \"beat note\" is already in use in another important connection (see Terminology Report, nineteen eleven) and the Committee recommends that those using the above terms shall say: \"This note is an on the beat note; this one is an after the beat note; this one a before the beat note.\"",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000074_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000074_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "DEFINITIONS",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "very low",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000077_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000077_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "Measure: A group of pulses.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "very low",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000078_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000078_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "Pulse Group: Two or more tones grouped within the pulse.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000080_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000080_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "This might include any unconventional motion which served to mark the movement of the music, whether made by conductor, performer or auditor.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000085_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000085_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "On the Beat Note (or rest): Any note (or rest) ranging in value from a full beat down, which calls for musical action (or inaction) synchronously with the conductor's beat.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "very low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000087_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000087_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "Before the Beat Note: Any note in a beat group which indicates that a tone is to be sounded after the middle of the pulse.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-fast_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "low",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-4958_11613_000088_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/4958/11613/4958_11613_000088_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4958",
        "content": "To illustrate terminology and to differentiate between Pulse and Beat as terms, respectively of ear and eye, the following is submitted:",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
